{panel:title=Status Update|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ff7f7f|titleBGColor=#ff7f7f|bgColor=#e5e5e5}
This feature request is currently tracked in JSWCLOUD-16901
{panel}

As a developer, I want to write a program that has access to the connections from a JIRA issue to the related branches, pull requests, commits, and builds so that I can automate more aspects of the deployment pipeline.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-15711].
  {panel}

Changing order of neighbour issues causes reranking of both issues. In worst case scenario this may lead to narrowing lexorank space between those issues. In order to improve this ranks of those issues could be swapped without direct reranking.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-15707].
  {panel}

h3. Summary

A LexoRank rebalance in large JIRA Software Data Centre instances can cause high CPU and Database utilisation across all nodes. I would like the ability to disable rebalancing during peak business hours (understanding that this may affect ranking on boards and the backlog), and enable it again during lower usage hours.
